  ><subfield code='a'
    >A Persian manuscript containing an abridgement of the poem, Shahnamah (Book of Kings). Written by the Persian poet Firdawsi around 1000 AD, it is the national epic of the Persian-speaking world. Its 60,000 rhyming couplets relate the story of the Persian kings, legendary and historical, the mythical and historical past of (Greater) Iran from the creation of the world up until the Islamic conquest of Persia in the 7th century.</subfield
    ></datafield
